{"lemma":"حَبْرِ","slug":"حَبْرِ","root":"ح.ب.ر","root_slug":"ح-ب-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ب-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":20},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n6871","n6872","n6873","n6874","n6875","n6876"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"ink"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"beauty"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make happy; to elate","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ink, to fill, cover, smear, mark, write, draw, illustrate, or outline with ink","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ink, to fill, cover, smear, mark, write, draw, illustrate, or outline with ink; to write","tags":["transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to improve the overall quality of (a text, a performance, a skill, and so on), to refine, to polish; to perfect","tags":["dated","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to improve the shape, form, style, structure, or composition of (handwriting, voice, and so on), to beautify; to embellish; to pretty; to improve in aspect or appearance, to make visually pleasing, to deck, to decorate, to ornament","tags":["dated","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to improve the shape, form, style, structure, or composition of (handwriting, voice, and so on), to beautify; to embellish; to pretty; to pattern (a garment); to embroider","tags":["dated","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become glad or happy, to cheer up, to brighten","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to become discolored (as if stained with ink), to become dark, to yellow","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَبَرَ (ḥabara) (form I)","tags":["form-of","intransitive","noun-from-verb","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ink, to fill, cover, smear, mark, write, draw, illustrate, or outline with ink","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to ink, to fill, cover, smear, mark, write, draw, illustrate, or outline with ink; to write (especially in an elegant style), to compose","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to better or improve in quality, appearance, etc. to enhance; to polish up; to perfect","tags":["dated","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to better or improve in quality, appearance, etc. to enhance; to polish up; to perfect; to prettify; to bedeck, to adorn","tags":["dated","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a scholar (especially one that is highly regarded and respected by a certain group and is deemed to be an authority)","tags":["broadly","countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a scholar (especially one that is highly regarded and respected by a certain group and is deemed to be an authority); the Scholar (one of the titles and designations of Ibn Abbas, one of companions of Muhammad)","tags":["broadly","countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a well-versed religious scribe; a learned theologian; a religious authority; a bishop","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a well-versed religious scribe; a learned theologian; a religious authority; a rabbi","tags":["Judaism","countable","intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a well-versed religious scribe; a learned theologian; a religious authority; an esteemed authoritative theologian, an imam","tags":["countable","intransitive","transitive"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Classical Syriac ܚܒܪܐ (ḥeḇrā, “ink”), from the root ܚ ܒ ܪ related to darkness. Merged with the root ح ب ر (ḥ b r).\n\nSenses related to ink, writing, and discoloration are from Etymology 1 (see above).\n\nDenominal verb of حِبْر (ḥibr, “ink”). Senses related to improvement, perfection, and embellishment are from or influenced by the root ح ب ر (ḥ b r) (see above).\n\nBorrowed from Biblical Hebrew חָבֵר (ḥɔḇer, “comrade”) in a specific meaning as used for sectarian cadres. Merged with Etymology 3 by analogy with the use of ink by religious clerks and scribes, hence \"a man of learning\", hence \"a scholarly theologian\", hence \"an authority in matters of religion\"."},"ipa":["/ħibr/","/ħab.ba.ra/","/ħabr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n6871","headword_ar":"حَبْرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places: ―         -b3-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, A, Msb, K, &c.;) but As says, I know not whether it be the former or the latter: (S:) IAar says both: A 'Obeyd says that some of the lawyers say the former; and some, the latter; (TA;) and that in his opinion it is the former: (S, TA:) AHeyth, that it is the former only: (TA:) Th mentions the former only: (Msb:) Fr says it is the latter only: (TA:) and the latter is [said to be] the more chaste because the pl. is of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEaAlN","text_ar":"اَفْعَالٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuEuwlN","text_ar":"فُعُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, TA:) [but a pl. of the latter measure is also mentioned:]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A learned man"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, Msb, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Jews:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether he be a Christian or Jewish or Sabean subject of a Muslim government, who pays a poll-tax for his freedom and toleration, or one who, having been such, has become a Muslim:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one skilled in the beautifying of language:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"righteous, man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Kaab, K, TA:) pl. (of the former, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) [but this is seldom used,] and (of the latter, Msb)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaArN","text_ar":"اَحْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (IDrst, S, A, Msb, K, &c.)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA","Msb","As","K","A","Kaab"]},{"entry_id":"n6872","headword_ar":"حِبْرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Ink,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"madaAdN","text_ar":"مَدَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"niqosN","text_ar":"نِقْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with which one writes:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) so called because it is one of the means of beautifying writings; (Mohammad Ibn-Zeyd, TA;) or because it beautifies, and makes plain, handwriting; (Hr, TA;) or because of the marks that it leaves: (As, TA:) pl. [of pauc.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaArN","text_ar":"اَحْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrst, TA) and [of mult.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wa$oYN","text_ar":"وَشْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"variegation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figuring,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of cloth or of a garment; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kind of variegated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured, cloth"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"garment"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (IAar, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibarapN","text_ar":"حِبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sign, of the enjoyment of ease and plenty:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, K: [in one copy of the S, and in the CK, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaru Aln~aEomapi","text_ar":"اَثَرُ النَّعْمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", I find, erroneously,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^avaru","text_ar":"اَثَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~iEomapi","text_ar":"النِّعْمَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":":]) and [hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, A, K;)"},{"kind":"page_break","n":499},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beauty of aspect;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a beautiful and pleasing aspect, that satisfies the eye by its comeliness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"colour; complexion:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, IAar, S, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaArN","text_ar":"اَحْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K, * TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~ahu laHasanu AlHibori waAls~ibori","text_ar":"اـِنَّهُ لَحَسَنُ الحِبْرِ وَالسِّبْرِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily he is beautiful, and of goodly appearance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of beautiful complexion."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*ahaba Hiboruhu","text_ar":"ذَهَبَ حِبْرُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wasiboruhu","text_ar":"وَسِبْرُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His colour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"complexion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"beautiful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and goodliness of form"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"aspect, departed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, S, A:) from the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='ati","text_ar":"جَا=ءَتِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^abilu Hasanapa AlA^aHobaAri waAlA^asobaAri","text_ar":"الاَبِلُ حَسَنَةَ الاَحْبَارِ وَالاَسْبَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The camels came beautiful in colours and in appearances"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Fr, S, A. *) One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAls~abori","text_ar":"وَالسَّبْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Hasanu AlHabori","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ حَسَنُ الحَبْرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": where"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hbr","text_ar":"حبر"},{"kind":"text","text":"seems to be the inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habarotuhu","text_ar":"حَبَرْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ I made him, or it, beautiful. ” (S.) ―         -b4-  Also, (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabarN","text_ar":"حَبَرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaArN","text_ar":"حَبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibaArN","text_ar":"حِبَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"trace,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K,) of beating, (A,) or of a blow that has not brought blood, or of a healed wound, (TA,) or of work, or labour: (A, TA:) pl. of the first [or second]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Yaakoob, S, K) and [of the first and third, accord. to analogy,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHobaArN","text_ar":"اَحْبَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;) and of the fourth"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabaAraAtN","text_ar":"حَبَارَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Yaakoob, S, TA,) it having no broken pl. (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bihi HubuwrN","text_ar":"بِهِ حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon him are marks"},{"kind":"text","text":"[of beating, &c.]. (S.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlD~arobi","text_ar":"الضَّرْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bijilodihi HibaAru","text_ar":"بِجِلْدِهِ حِبَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon his skin is the mark of beating."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEamali","text_ar":"العَمَلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biyadihi HibaAru","text_ar":"بِيَدِهِ حِبَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Upon his hand is the mark of work,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"labour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b5-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b6-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A2-  Also, [like the Hebrew"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"},{"kind":"text","text":", and the Chaldee"},{"kind":"text","text":"?"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A like; an equal; a fellow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","As","TA","IDrst","IAar","Fr","A"]},{"entry_id":"n6873","headword_ar":"حَبَرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":       -A2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibarapN","text_ar":"حِبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6874","headword_ar":"حَبِرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabiyrN","text_ar":"حَبِيرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6875","headword_ar":"حِبَرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibarapN","text_ar":"حِبَرَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n6876","headword_ar":"حِبِرٌ","root":"Hbr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) the only subst. of this form beside"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ibilN","text_ar":"اـِبِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) [and a few rare dial. vars.,] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirapN","text_ar":"حِبِرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborapN","text_ar":"حَبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HuborapN","text_ar":"حُبْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HibirN","text_ar":"حِبِرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiborN","text_ar":"حِبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaborN","text_ar":"حَبْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",] is a pl. [or rather a coll. gen. n.], (S,) and with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"it is said to be a n. un. ; (Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A yellowness that mingles with the whiteness of the teeth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a yellowness of the teeth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, A, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaHN","text_ar":"قَلَحٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the teeth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qalaHN","text_ar":"قَلَحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is when they become green: and when the crust increases so as to encroach upon the gums, and to make the roots of the teeth to appear, this is what is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaforN","text_ar":"حَفْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HafarN","text_ar":"حَفَرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Sh, Msb, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HubuwrN","text_ar":"حُبُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","A","S","Sh","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}